files.Title: ShapeEngine.Core.CollisionSystem.Collision
files.Summary: Contains the information of an intersection or an overlap between two colliders.

files.Title: ShapeEngine.Core.CollisionSystem.CollisionInformation
files.Summary: Contains the information of a collision between two collision objects in form of a list of collisions. Each collision is an intersection or overlap between two colliders

files.Title: ShapeEngine.Core.CollisionSystem.CollisionPointsFilterType
files.Summary: First - Selects the first collision point. Closest - Selects the collision point closest to the reference point. Furthest - Selects the collision point furthest from the reference point. Combined - Computes the average collision point. PointingTowards - Selects the collision point with a normal pointing the most towards the reference position. PointingAway - Selects the collision point with a normal pointing the most away from the reference position. Random - Selects a random collision point.

files.Title: ShapeEngine.Core.Shapes.Polygon
files.Summary: Points shoud be in CCW order.

files.Title: ShapeEngine.Core.Shapes.Quad
files.Summary: Points should be in CCW order (A -> B -> C -> D)

files.Title: ShapeEngine.Core.Shapes.Triangle
files.Summary: Class that represents a triangle by holding three points. Points a, b, c should be in ccw order!

files.Title: ShapeEngine.Core.SpawnArea
files.Summary: Provides a simple area for managing adding/removing, updating, and drawing of area objects. Does not provide a collision system.

files.Title: ShapeEngine.Core.Structs.AnchorPoint
files.Summary: Used for ui anchor points and rect alignments. 0, 0 is top left, 1, 1 is bottom right.

files.Title: ShapeEngine.Core.Structs.ExitCode
files.Summary: Returned by the Run() function in the GameLoop class.

files.Title: ShapeEngine.Core.Structs.GappedOutlineDrawingInfo
files.Summary: Used for DrawGappedOutline functions.

files.Title: ShapeEngine.Core.Structs.LineCapType
files.Summary: Determines how the end of a line is drawn.

files.Title: ShapeEngine.Core.Structs.LineDrawingInfo
files.Summary: Used for defining how a line is drawn.

files.Title: ShapeEngine.Core.TextureSurface
files.Summary: Allows you to create a render texture and draw to its surface. The texture can not be resized after creation and has to be manually unloaded. Multiple functions allow you to draw to the texture (or part of it) to the screen. UseBegin/EndDraw to draw to the texture with any drawing functions.

files.Title: ShapeEngine.Input.InputEventHandler.InputEventCallback
files.Summary: Callback for receiving input events. Should return if input event should propagate further down.

files.Title: ShapeEngine.Persistent.ContentLoader
files.Summary: Provides a simple wraper to load all types of Raylib resources and json string.

files.Title: ShapeEngine.Persistent.ContentManager

files.Title: ShapeEngine.Persistent.ContentManagerPacked
files.Summary: Provides a simple class to load content that was packed with the ContentPacker.

files.Title: ShapeEngine.Persistent.ContentPacker
files.Summary: Can be used to pack resources in a folder structur into a single txt file. Every resource consists of 2 lines the resulting txt file. The first line is the name with extension the second line is data as encoded string.

files.Title: ShapeEngine.Persistent.SavegameObject
files.Summary: Simple base class for a savegame object. To serialize and save class every property needs to have public getter and setter!

files.Title: ShapeEngine.Timing.Repeater.RepeaterFunc
